.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk support" 1 20%E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk support \- send a support request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Bc bk support [\-t] [
.ARG email@host ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Send a request to BitMover support.
.LP
The default behavior is to display the graphical version of the support
form when the DISPLAY environment variable is set (UNIX) or if it is
run on a Windows operating system.
To use a text editor rather than the gui, use the -t option.
.LP
If email address is specified, the support request will be sent to that
email address.
.LP
This command should be used to request support report rather then sending
mail to support@bitmover.com or one of the developers.
.LP
The \*(BK support request form is online at
.B http://www.bitkeeper.com/support
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-t
Use a text editor rather than the default graphical tool to fill out a support
report.
.SH EXAMPLE
An example text template looks like this:
.sp
.nf
Program:
        [cset, co, delta, etc.  or what you were doing, like 'installing']

Release:
        beta10-pre1

OS:
        [Linux, IRIX, NT, etc]
Etc.
.sp
.fi
and the filled out report should look like this (note that the data
goes after the tags, not on the same line):
.sp
.nf
Program:
        support

Release:
        pre-2.0-2

OS:
        All
Etc.
.sp
.fi
.SH CATEGORY
.B Admin
